HEADWORD: Lodestone
<hw>Lode"stone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Load</ets>, <ets>lode</ets> +
<ets>stone</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A piece of magnetite, a
magnetic iron ore, possessing polarity like a magnetic needle, having
the power to attract as well as to be attracted magnetically. See
<er>Magnetite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

